00:32.101 --> 00:34.972
- Can I help you?
- Well, I called for her last night.

00:36.564 --> 00:38.224
Her husband died last night.

00:38.817 --> 00:41.882
His picture was in the paper once,
but you misspelled his name.

00:41.986 --> 00:43.967
She wants to be sure you get it right.

00:44.072 --> 00:47.304
- You see, it's not one, but two "I"s.
- You want obituaries.

00:47.408 --> 00:49.982
It's the guy in the back
with the urn on his desk.

00:52.330 --> 00:54.453
What funeral home was she taken to?

00:55.333 --> 00:56.448
How old was she?

00:59.045 --> 01:00.290
What did she die of?

01:01.422 --> 01:04.542
Well, I have to know what she died of
or I can't write the obit.

01:05.385 --> 01:06.962
I don't make the rules.

01:07.887 --> 01:10.378
Could I call you back? Thank you.

01:17.021 --> 01:18.432
Excuse me, will you?

01:20.733 --> 01:21.764
Tom?

01:22.569 --> 01:24.884
Tom, look, I cannot take this anymore.

01:24.988 --> 01:28.303
You got to get me off the obit desk.
I can't write another obituary.

01:28.408 --> 01:31.390
Calm down, Adam. Relax.
It isn't going to last forever.

01:31.494 --> 01:32.766
Think of it this way:

01:32.871 --> 01:37.118
This is your last chance in journalism
to write anything nice about anybody.

01:38.126 --> 01:39.122
Perfect.

03:02.877 --> 03:04.900
New York City - Five Years Later

03:05.004 --> 03:06.986
So, you can't talk to me about the arrest.

03:07.090 --> 03:10.791
Can you talk to me about after the arrest?
You know, his time in prison.

03:10.969 --> 03:12.249
It was terrible.

03:12.929 --> 03:15.337
He was in shock the entire time.

03:17.100 --> 03:19.971
He lost a lot of weight
because he couldn't eat the food.

03:21.187 --> 03:22.350
He couldn't sleep.

03:23.022 --> 03:26.308
They had him in the same cell
with a Mafia hit man.

03:27.026 --> 03:29.980
- He was afraid to close his eyes for a week.
- Interesting.

03:30.446 --> 03:31.941
For a man like him...

03:32.657 --> 03:34.863
that was cruel and unusual punishment.

03:35.535 --> 03:36.863
I'll say.

03:37.912 --> 03:41.079
What do you think, Charlie?
Can you get him to talk to me?

03:41.708 --> 03:43.950
He's not talking to any press, Adam.

03:44.627 --> 03:46.122
He doesn't trust you guys.

03:46.588 --> 03:47.750
I don't blame him.

03:48.381 --> 03:50.421
There's been a lot of bad press lately.

03:50.967 --> 03:53.615
I thought he'd want to tell
his side of the story.

03:53.720 --> 03:55.826
The only way to do that is an interview.

03:55.930 --> 03:59.382
Especially if he feels that the government
is screwing around on him.

03:59.767 --> 04:02.389
Now, I didn't exactly say that.

04:03.730 --> 04:06.102
Anyway, not for the record.

04:06.649 --> 04:09.223
I don't want you to twist
what I said out of shape.

04:09.861 --> 04:10.940
Right.

04:12.071 --> 04:15.888
The problem is, the only people that
will talk to me are people that hate him.

04:15.992 --> 04:18.661
And I'm doing this story
whether I talk to him or not.

04:19.077 --> 04:21.451
So don't fault me
if this is a negative piece.

04:22.499 --> 04:24.521
That sounds vaguely like a threat.

04:24.626 --> 04:28.754
No, I think that if he wants a chance,
he's got to turn his press around.

04:30.715 --> 04:33.123
You reporters think
you make the world turn.

04:33.551 --> 04:34.927
I don't know about that.

04:35.595 --> 04:38.133
You know,
I used to be a reporter myself...

04:38.806 --> 04:41.095
until I got tired of starving my family.

04:41.518 --> 04:44.187
That's why I got into public relations.

04:44.854 --> 04:48.603
- To make a living wage. I love it.
- Yeah.

04:48.983 --> 04:50.181
I really do.

04:53.029 --> 04:55.816
Excuse me. I have to take a piss.

05:36.364 --> 05:40.065
- Am I interrupting something?
- No. Adam, come on in and look at this.

05:48.376 --> 05:51.942
- Frankie strikes again.
- Look at that. They're good.

05:52.046 --> 05:54.882
At last someone has managed
to capture his true essence.

05:55.008 --> 05:58.240
Look at this one.
I can't believe that she got him to do this.

05:58.344 --> 06:00.004
Believe me, it was easy.

06:01.764 --> 06:04.220
I think this will be the one
we use on the cover.

06:05.810 --> 06:07.435
- You like it?
- I like it.

06:07.896 --> 06:09.710
- You want to get some lunch?
- Yeah.

06:09.814 --> 06:12.087
- Frankie, you want to join us?
- Absolutely.

06:12.192 --> 06:13.922
How did it go this morning?

06:14.027 --> 06:14.965
Fascinating.

06:15.069 --> 06:18.719
He insisted we meet at the Atrium Club,
saying it was a safe place to talk.

06:18.823 --> 06:22.765
He implied the government had a reason
for putting McKenzie out of business.

06:22.869 --> 06:24.016
He was so nervous.

06:24.120 --> 06:27.121
- But what about the interview?
- He thought it was doubtful.

06:27.415 --> 06:30.481
- There's no story without an interview.
- Or without pictures.

06:30.585 --> 06:33.400
You don't want to recycle
the same wire service photos.

06:33.505 --> 06:36.904
- I'd love to shoot him.
- You'd make him pose with coke in his lap.

06:37.008 --> 06:40.294
- I can make him do anything.
- Come on, you guys.

06:48.186 --> 06:48.999
I have an idea.

06:49.103 --> 06:52.722
McKenzie has a hearing tomorrow,
in Los Angeles, to reduce his bail.

06:52.857 --> 06:55.255
But he needs the $2 million
to pay his lawyers.

06:55.360 --> 06:58.133
Why don't I fly out there tonight
and get the interview?

06:58.238 --> 07:01.303
- You hate flying.
- I'm fine, as long as there's no turbulence.

07:01.407 --> 07:03.764
When it starts bouncing around,
I get drunk.

07:03.868 --> 07:07.351
If you're going, let's find a story
for you to do at the same time...

07:07.455 --> 07:11.583
in case it doesn't work out. I don't want
you wasting your time or my money.

07:11.709 --> 07:14.960
You cheap fuck.
You want two stories for the price of one?

07:15.088 --> 07:16.026
Fine.

07:16.130 --> 07:19.321
I have an idea for a story
that would take place in California.

07:19.425 --> 07:20.197
What?

07:20.301 --> 07:22.700
I got the idea at the Atrium Club,
this morning.

07:22.804 --> 07:25.285
- Who would you be going after?
- Not who, what.

07:25.390 --> 07:28.307
- Excuse me, what will you be going after?
- Health clubs.

07:28.768 --> 07:30.082
- Groan.
- No.

07:30.186 --> 07:33.961
I'll do a story about how they're
turning into the singles bars of the '80s?

07:34.065 --> 07:36.296
Find a couple.
Do a non-fiction love story.

07:36.401 --> 07:39.341
- With pictures.
- Lots of them. It could be hilarious.

07:39.445 --> 07:43.178
Particularly set in Los Angeles.
You know, inflated bodies. Airheads.

07:43.283 --> 07:45.431
- Hot tubs? Alfalfa sprouts?
- Absolutely.

07:45.535 --> 07:48.475
We haven't done L.A. in a long time.
It would be wonderful.

07:48.580 --> 07:49.825
- Sounds great.
- Shit.

07:49.998 --> 07:52.313
- What?
- Carly Simon just walked in.

07:52.417 --> 07:53.330
Oh, God.

07:53.501 --> 07:57.499
- She hated the story you did on her.
- I know, I know.

08:13.980 --> 08:15.723
- Hi, Carly.
- Hi, Carly.

08:16.107 --> 08:17.021
Hi, Carly.

08:17.484 --> 08:20.591
- I read that shit you wrote about me.
- Come on, Carly.

08:20.695 --> 08:24.230
The only thing worse than being
written about is not being written about.

08:44.969 --> 08:47.756
There is a motion with respect to the bail
for Mr. McKenzie.

08:47.889 --> 08:49.745
- Is that correct?
- It is, Your Honour.

08:49.849 --> 08:51.889
- Yes. Is there a written motion?
- No.

08:53.645 --> 08:55.417
I'd like to make an oral presentation.

08:55.522 --> 08:57.561
- You filed the notice?
- Yes, Your Honour.

08:57.690 --> 09:00.089
All right, then, go ahead
and state your reasons.

09:00.193 --> 09:01.901
Then the government may reply.

09:02.070 --> 09:05.236
We are seeking a reduction in bail
based on two major things:

09:05.615 --> 09:09.280
One, Mr. McKenzie is simply
not as wealthy as the government...

09:09.410 --> 09:11.642
and the press, for that matter, imagines.

09:11.746 --> 09:15.411
Let's leave the press out of it.
They have nothing to do with setting bail.

09:16.209 --> 09:17.917
Here they come.

09:24.592 --> 09:27.908
- Charlie, what about the interview?
- He's not talking to anybody.

09:28.012 --> 09:30.744
- Period.
- If he changes his mind, I'll be at...

09:30.849 --> 09:33.803
He's not changing his mind.
He's flying to New York today.

09:34.352 --> 09:35.930
The Sunset Marquis.

09:36.855 --> 09:38.265
The Sunset Marquis!

09:57.167 --> 09:57.938
Hello.

09:58.042 --> 09:59.667
- <i>Adam?</i>
- Yeah.

09:59.794 --> 10:02.166
- <i>How's it going?</i>
- It's going fine.

10:02.297 --> 10:04.820
He got his bail reduced,
but I couldn't talk to him.

10:04.924 --> 10:06.655
He had to go back to New York.

10:06.759 --> 10:10.534
I'm working on some other angles.
I'm trying to locate some friends of his.

10:10.638 --> 10:12.595
I started the piece. It's real good.

10:12.765 --> 10:16.123
- In other words, no interview?
- Come on, Mark, please.

10:16.227 --> 10:18.959
The story is great,
and the material I have is terrific.

10:19.063 --> 10:22.755
- It should be a cover.
- You get the interview and we'll talk cover.

10:22.859 --> 10:26.192
Simon & Schuster just made an inquiry
for me to do this as a book.

10:26.488 --> 10:27.593
Cover would help.

10:27.697 --> 10:29.903
I'm not in the goddamn book business.

10:30.492 --> 10:34.276
- Have you found a health club yet?
- <i>Yes, I found an ad in the phone book.</i>

10:35.038 --> 10:37.161
The club's name is The Sports Connection.

10:37.624 --> 10:40.459
"Health club, racquetball, and good times.

10:40.710 --> 10:42.983
"We're a totally new concept
in athletic club.

10:43.087 --> 10:45.527
"We're more than a club,
we're a lifestyle."

10:45.632 --> 10:49.581
Then it has this illustration of a couple
in sports clothes hugging each other.

10:50.053 --> 10:51.084
It sounds perfect.

10:52.555 --> 10:54.787
<i>What kind of story are you planning to do?</i>

10:54.891 --> 10:58.040
<i>Maybe something about
couples meeting here, falling in love</i>

10:58.144 --> 11:00.292
- <i>getting married.</i>
- <i>That sounds good.</i>

11:00.396 --> 11:04.046
<i>Let's go down and get you a membership,
so you can see what's happening.</i>

11:04.150 --> 11:05.728
<i>Now that sounds even better.</i>

11:06.694 --> 11:09.551
Nanette, where did you get this idea
to make this place...

11:09.656 --> 11:12.147
more than a health club,
like your ad says?

11:12.283 --> 11:16.392
I looked around the city and I saw
that people had had it with singles bars.

11:16.496 --> 11:19.687
They even had the supermarkets
staked out. That was getting boring.

11:19.791 --> 11:20.521
Really?

11:20.625 --> 11:24.316
There wasn't anywhere people could
get together in a healthy environment...

11:24.420 --> 11:26.413
and have some social interaction.

11:28.091 --> 11:30.463
- Right.
- Mr. Lawrence, hold it.

11:31.177 --> 11:34.785
Michael and I, he's my partner,
thought it'd be great to create a place...

11:34.889 --> 11:37.538
like the lodge at the bottom of the hill
in Aspen.

11:37.642 --> 11:39.957
Where people could share
a common interest.

11:40.061 --> 11:41.583
- All right.
- Phone, Nanette.

11:41.688 --> 11:43.252
- Take a message, okay?
- Okay.

11:43.356 --> 11:46.380
My concept was to get people
out of their potato chip bags...

11:46.484 --> 11:50.009
into the club by convincing them
it didn't have to be drudgery.

11:50.113 --> 11:51.719
- That it could be fun.
- Right.

11:51.823 --> 11:54.444
- I'll get somebody to show you around.
- Sounds good.

11:55.869 --> 11:59.949
We have nine racquetball courts.
These two courts are our challenge courts.

12:00.081 --> 12:02.521
- The winner stays on, loser gets off.
- Really?

12:02.625 --> 12:04.231
Then, you have a lounge area.

12:04.335 --> 12:07.870
It's a good place to sit and relax,
before and after your workout.

12:08.256 --> 12:11.127
Your entrance and registration area.

12:11.968 --> 12:15.951
And then we have Pete's Pro Shop.
They have the latest in workout apparel...

12:16.055 --> 12:17.882
and racquetball equipment.

12:18.183 --> 12:21.749
Then you have the snack bar.
They have fruit juices, great smoothies.

12:21.853 --> 12:23.876
- Beer and wine?
- No wine, just beer.

12:23.980 --> 12:26.253
- You can get a beer after your workout.
- Good.

12:26.357 --> 12:28.213
- And great sandwiches.
- Sprouts?

12:28.318 --> 12:29.423
- Definitely.
- Yes.

12:29.527 --> 12:31.884
- Are you into health food?
- No, not really.

12:31.988 --> 12:34.136
Okay, let's look at Body Dynamics.

12:34.240 --> 12:36.889
What they do in here
is personal fitness assessments.

12:36.993 --> 12:40.267
They do cardiovascular testing,
nutritional analysis...

12:40.371 --> 12:43.354
hydrostatic weighing,
or weighing the body underwater.

12:43.458 --> 12:45.773
It helps determine
your percentage of body fat.

12:45.877 --> 12:47.870
Then, you have
an hour-and-a-half-long consultation.

12:48.963 --> 12:52.738
- And here we have the coed gym.
- So this is where all the action takes place.

12:52.842 --> 12:55.199
On the free weights,
the universal equipment...

12:55.303 --> 12:57.409
the Nautilus, and Icarian equipment.

12:57.514 --> 13:00.996
- I feel guilty, all these people working out.
- And the Lifecycle bikes.

13:01.100 --> 13:02.665
- Hi, Bobby.
- Hi, Linda.

13:02.769 --> 13:06.418
- I miss you. I never see you anymore.
- Adam, Linda. Linda, Adam.

13:06.523 --> 13:07.518
Hello, Linda.

13:07.857 --> 13:09.517
I mean it. I really miss you.

13:09.984 --> 13:13.384
I worked up here as an instructor
before I was promoted to sales.

13:13.488 --> 13:16.061
- I see.
- He used to work on my body.

13:16.991 --> 13:18.806
- Looking good.
- God knows, I try.

13:18.910 --> 13:22.955
I'm still in the "before" group,
not the "after," but I'm gonna get there.

13:23.623 --> 13:26.624
- Where's Sally?
- She's there, working out with Roger.

13:27.293 --> 13:29.963
- Trying to make her tits even bigger.
- Well, see you.

13:30.839 --> 13:32.569
- Nice meeting you.
- You, too.

13:32.674 --> 13:35.114
- What's her story?
- She was a mess.

13:35.218 --> 13:38.283
- What do you mean?
- No one works as hard to get in shape.

13:38.388 --> 13:40.795
- Really?
- Hi, Sally. Hi, Roger.

13:41.307 --> 13:43.872
- Five.
- He's killing me.

13:43.977 --> 13:47.809
- Come on, let's go, back to work.
- How many? Just three more.

13:48.773 --> 13:51.338
- That's a couple you should talk to.
- Who are they?

13:51.442 --> 13:54.258
Sally works with Linda
at the Apparel Mart, downtown.

13:54.362 --> 13:56.760
And Roger,
he's a stripper at Chippendales.

13:56.865 --> 14:00.364
- Interesting. I do want to talk to them.
- Nice people. They met here.

14:00.910 --> 14:04.059
- You'll have such a good time, I promise.
- Come on, come on!

14:04.164 --> 14:06.203
How big do you want them?

14:06.416 --> 14:09.898
Can I get a list of couples that met here,
and their phone numbers?

14:10.003 --> 14:13.444
- It's against policy to give phone numbers.
- Can't you bend the rules?

14:13.548 --> 14:15.195
I really don't have much time.

14:15.300 --> 14:17.156
- I'll see what I can do.
- Thank you.

14:17.260 --> 14:19.867
- Kenny, this is Adam Lawrence.
- How you doing?

14:19.971 --> 14:24.163
He's a reporter for <i>Rolling Stone.</i>
Kenny can answer questions if I'm not in.

14:24.267 --> 14:26.972
- Nanette said you're looking for couples.
- Yeah.

14:27.228 --> 14:28.667
I'm a big fan of yours.

14:28.771 --> 14:31.003
- Really?
- Yeah, I subscribe to <i>Rolling Stone.</i>

14:31.107 --> 14:34.340
I read your piece on Carly Simon.
I thought it was great.

14:34.444 --> 14:35.689
So did I.

14:41.910 --> 14:44.475
I bet lots of lustful matinees
get started here.

14:44.579 --> 14:49.407
- What? What do you mean?
- Excuse me, I mean, social interaction.

14:49.876 --> 14:52.165
- Let me show you the rest of the club.
- Okay.

14:52.837 --> 14:55.079
By the way,
what kind of story are you writing?

15:04.641 --> 15:07.048
This is aerobics and "slimnastics."

15:13.316 --> 15:14.596
That's Jessie Wilson.

15:14.859 --> 15:17.944
She's probably the best female instructor
we got right now.

15:21.866 --> 15:24.274
They call her "the Aerobics Pied Piper."

15:24.702 --> 15:27.324
- A lot of couples met in her class.
- Really?

15:30.708 --> 15:32.037
Turn it around.

15:35.588 --> 15:37.194
I'm going back to my workout.

15:37.298 --> 15:38.821
- Enjoy the class.
- Thanks.

15:38.925 --> 15:41.381
- Nice meeting you.
- It was very nice meeting you.

15:49.102 --> 15:51.675
Squeeze. Release. Squeeze. Release.

15:54.649 --> 15:55.894
Toes out!

16:00.613 --> 16:02.108
Shoulders down.

16:13.626 --> 16:15.334
Really tighten your thighs!

16:29.934 --> 16:31.049
Touch down!

16:35.023 --> 16:37.062
Straight leg, left. Go!

16:41.321 --> 16:43.112
Hold it down on two...

16:47.911 --> 16:49.239
Hold it!

16:53.249 --> 16:54.163
Let's go!

16:56.628 --> 16:58.537
- 'Night, Kim.
- Goodnight, Jessie.

16:59.339 --> 17:01.166
- Hi, Shirley.
- Hi, Jessie.

17:02.383 --> 17:03.297
Jessie.

17:03.676 --> 17:05.782
- Adam Lawrence. Hi.
- Hi.

17:05.887 --> 17:08.757
- I really enjoyed your class. You're great.
- Thanks.

17:09.348 --> 17:12.931
I'm a reporter for <i>Rolling Stone.</i>
I'm writing on the Sports Connection.

17:13.269 --> 17:14.249
- Really?
- Yeah.

17:14.354 --> 17:15.978
- <i>Rolling Stone</i> ?
- Yes.

17:16.647 --> 17:18.190
I'd love to interview you.

17:18.858 --> 17:20.233
- Why?
- Why not?

17:21.027 --> 17:24.561
- I can think of a lot of reasons.
- It would be good for business.

17:25.073 --> 17:26.318
Business is fine.

17:28.367 --> 17:30.989
You think about it.
I'll be around for a few days.

17:31.329 --> 17:34.034
I will, but I don't change my mind
about anything.

17:35.291 --> 17:36.999
Could you give me a reason why?

17:39.212 --> 17:40.754
I read magazines.

17:51.766 --> 17:55.040
<i>The Star Garden Club
is proud to present...</i>

17:55.145 --> 17:59.391
<i>direct from New York City,
the one and only...</i>

17:59.691 --> 18:00.971
<i>Shotsy.</i>

18:59.876 --> 19:01.774
- Jessie, hi.
- Hi.

19:01.878 --> 19:04.026
- Did you think about it?
- Very, very hard.

19:04.130 --> 19:05.874
- Did you change your mind?
- No.

19:06.508 --> 19:09.544
- Well, I'll get someone else to interview.
- I guess you will.

19:09.719 --> 19:13.035
Maybe you don't understand.
I may want you as the focus of my story.

19:13.139 --> 19:16.555
No, you don't understand.
I don't want to be the focus of anything.

19:16.768 --> 19:20.334
Okay, you don't have to be the focus.
I just need your viewpoint.

19:20.438 --> 19:23.128
Last time I counted,
there were 90 aerobic instructors.

19:23.233 --> 19:27.383
- But your classes are the biggest, sexiest...
- Are you deaf? No!

19:27.487 --> 19:29.978
- What's the problem?
- I was burned once.

19:30.281 --> 19:32.108
I don't intend to get burned again.

19:33.910 --> 19:38.406
- The battery's dead.
- No kidding. It happens all the time.

19:39.415 --> 19:40.874
Where's your car?

19:42.961 --> 19:44.787
I have jumper cables.

19:46.589 --> 19:47.653
- You okay?
- Yeah.

19:47.757 --> 19:51.340
I can never remember
which is positive or negative. Try that.

19:53.346 --> 19:55.255
- All right.
- Keep it going.

19:59.644 --> 20:01.684
Okay, I have an idea.

20:02.313 --> 20:04.461
I know you don't want to be interviewed.

20:04.566 --> 20:06.938
- But how about dinner tonight?
- Sorry.

20:07.735 --> 20:09.313
How about lunch tomorrow?

20:09.863 --> 20:12.318
- All off the record?
- Just like regular people.

20:21.374 --> 20:22.855
- Hello.
- Hi.

20:22.959 --> 20:25.733
I'm sorry to call so late,
but I just got your message.

20:25.837 --> 20:27.067
What's going on?

20:27.172 --> 20:29.045
- <i>Are you all right?</i>
- Yeah. Why?

20:29.382 --> 20:31.458
Hold on, I'm putting you on speaker.

20:32.510 --> 20:36.327
I got a call from a guy I know who's in
the shady end of the record business.

20:36.431 --> 20:40.164
He said you're ringing the wrong doorbells
and might end up in the hospital.

20:40.268 --> 20:41.466
Make sense to you?

20:41.769 --> 20:44.474
I don't know.
I've been poking around, but...

20:45.398 --> 20:48.422
I made contact
with one of his old girlfriends today.

20:48.526 --> 20:50.685
Maybe somebody's nervous about that.

20:50.945 --> 20:53.152
I called just to say watch yourself.

20:53.406 --> 20:56.638
I want you to promise me
you'll be real careful on this one, okay?

20:56.743 --> 20:59.316
Anyway, how's the other one?
Have you found a hook?

20:59.537 --> 21:02.645
Yeah, as a matter of fact.
I found this terrific opportunity.

21:02.749 --> 21:06.699
It's not the kind of story I had in mind
at first, but it's pretty good. Listen.

21:07.003 --> 21:11.665
There's a girl at the Sports Connection
who they call "the Aerobics Pied Piper."

21:12.050 --> 21:14.657
She's got this following
of leotards and sweat suits.

21:14.761 --> 21:17.368
She's fun to watch,
so lots of couples meet there.

21:17.472 --> 21:19.678
Sounds good. Maybe that will work.

21:19.974 --> 21:23.178
It's great. The only problem is
she doesn't want to cooperate.

21:23.353 --> 21:25.751
- But she will.
- I'm sure she will.

21:25.855 --> 21:29.639
Just remember, get close to her
while you research, but when you write...

21:29.943 --> 21:33.857
Forget she has a mother. Right.
Don't I always?

21:34.072 --> 21:36.195
- Talk to you later.
- <i>'Bye.</i>

21:38.952 --> 21:41.953
So, who's going to get
the Lawrence treatment this time?

21:42.413 --> 21:43.694
Some girl he met.

21:45.166 --> 21:48.167
- That's obvious.
- So what's the hook of your story?

21:48.586 --> 21:52.403
It's not one of those pieces about how
health clubs are the new singles bars?

21:52.507 --> 21:53.420
God forbid.

21:54.133 --> 21:57.716
- Do you work out?
- Yes, I do work out, when I have time.

21:58.221 --> 22:01.578
I don't take it as seriously
as you guys do, but I do work out.

22:01.683 --> 22:04.957
My dad didn't take it seriously, either.
He died fat at 40.

22:05.061 --> 22:05.761
Sorry.

22:06.813 --> 22:09.086
I was 8. I knew even then...

22:09.190 --> 22:12.381
if he had worked out and not smoked,
he'd have lived longer.

22:12.485 --> 22:13.564
How old are you?

22:14.904 --> 22:17.442
I'm sorry.
You don't have to answer that question.

22:19.993 --> 22:22.365
- Mid to late 20s.
- Interesting.

22:22.745 --> 22:23.600
What?

22:23.705 --> 22:26.145
Most people I've interviewed
are about that age.

22:26.249 --> 22:29.369
I think when you get to our age
you feel the need to keep in shape.

22:29.961 --> 22:32.693
Probably no coincidence
that the baby-boom generation...

22:32.797 --> 22:35.881
approached 30 at the same time
as the exercise boom started.

22:36.342 --> 22:38.252
- You do have a hook?
- Maybe.

22:38.845 --> 22:42.786
It's good to talk a story out before writing.
It's all spitballing at this point.

22:42.891 --> 22:44.538
- What's that?
- A tape recorder.

22:44.642 --> 22:47.374
I thought maybe we'd exchange ideas,
if you don't mind.

22:47.479 --> 22:48.677
- Do you mind?
- Yeah.

22:49.856 --> 22:51.628
- I won't do it.
- Thanks.

22:51.733 --> 22:54.298
I do have some notes
that may interest you.

22:54.402 --> 22:55.382
Look at this.

22:55.487 --> 22:58.385
"The baby-boomers are leading
a physical great awakening...

22:58.490 --> 23:02.736
"like the spiritual awakenings
that grip America about every 100 years."

23:04.287 --> 23:05.225
Pretty good.

23:05.330 --> 23:10.397
I think people want to take responsibility
instead of leaning on institutions.

23:10.502 --> 23:13.942
For instance, does anyone believe
the government will take care of us?

23:14.047 --> 23:17.498
- No.
- Not since Vietnam or Watergate, no.

23:17.967 --> 23:22.713
Or big corporations? Or even doctors?
So, you have to take care of yourself.

23:23.097 --> 23:26.264
A lot of people are trying to get in shape,
as you well know.

23:26.643 --> 23:28.332
I think we've come full circle.

23:28.436 --> 23:31.354
Almost back to Emersonian America
of self-reliance.

23:31.815 --> 23:33.392
There's something else here.

23:33.942 --> 23:37.800
Emerson: "Do that which is assigned thee
and thou canst not hope too much...

23:37.904 --> 23:39.315
"or dare too much."

23:40.156 --> 23:44.973
So, what could be more all-American,
more old-fashioned all-American...

23:45.078 --> 23:47.643
than institutions
like the Sports Connection?

23:47.747 --> 23:51.959
Little capitals of Emersonian America
scattered from sea to shining sea.

23:53.419 --> 23:54.618
You are so hot.

24:00.218 --> 24:02.408
I'm glad we had this off-the-record lunch.

24:02.512 --> 24:05.797
I was real suspicious of the kind of story
you were going to write.

24:06.015 --> 24:08.497
If you want to know
about the Sports Connection...

24:08.601 --> 24:10.624
a real writer would work out. Join.

24:10.728 --> 24:12.710
- You ever taken an aerobic class?
- No.

24:12.814 --> 24:15.379
I've got one starting soon.
You should take one of mine.

24:15.483 --> 24:19.675
I should, but I can't, I don't have the time.
I've another appointment this afternoon.

24:19.779 --> 24:23.887
I have to finish up a story
before I can concentrate on this one.

24:23.992 --> 24:26.613
- What's the other story?
- Joseph McKenzie.

24:27.412 --> 24:28.989
You do important stuff, too?

24:30.123 --> 24:32.813
- Will you be here later?
- Nope. I'm on the road.

24:32.917 --> 24:34.481
What do you mean, on the road?

24:34.586 --> 24:37.735
I teach class at the
Beverly Hills Sports Connection, tonight.

24:37.839 --> 24:40.321
- Coming in?
- No, I really don't have the time.

24:40.425 --> 24:42.216
I'll make a deal with you, though.

24:42.343 --> 24:47.301
I would gladly take one of your aerobic
classes if you'd let me interview you.

24:49.392 --> 24:51.515
I was really beginning to like you, too.

25:17.378 --> 25:18.484
Notes on lunch.

25:18.588 --> 25:22.029
We talked about baby-boom generation,
great physical awakening...

25:22.133 --> 25:23.758
Emersonian America.

25:24.302 --> 25:25.927
Father dies fat at 40.

25:26.221 --> 25:29.803
Interesting girl.
She's smart, but I've got to be smarter.

25:31.726 --> 25:33.600
McKenzie and I go way back.

25:34.103 --> 25:37.628
I met him when I was in New York,
and I was stripping, even then.

25:37.732 --> 25:40.057
Right, but in a little classier club.

25:40.652 --> 25:43.985
I didn't know who he was
and he walks into the club one night...

25:44.280 --> 25:46.512
and he puts a $1,000 bill in my G-string.

25:46.616 --> 25:49.237
- Are you kidding? Really?
- We had a lot of fun.

25:49.536 --> 25:51.659
- He's really a great guy.
- Sounds it.

25:52.956 --> 25:55.562
I'll tell you something,
if you promise not to tell.

25:55.667 --> 25:58.273
- Okay.
- He bought this house for me.

25:58.378 --> 25:59.733
- Really?
- Yes.

25:59.838 --> 26:03.420
- Well, do you still talk to him?
- Joe and I talk all the time.

26:04.175 --> 26:06.464
- Shotsy?
- My God, my husband's home.

26:06.928 --> 26:08.422
Eddie?

26:09.305 --> 26:11.078
- Honey, this is Adam Lawrence.
- Hi.

26:11.182 --> 26:14.790
He's a reporter for <i>Rolling Stone</i>,
and he's doing a piece on Joe McKenzie.

26:14.894 --> 26:18.377
- Get out of here.
- I wanted to ask your wife a few questions.

26:18.481 --> 26:20.963
- You leave her out of this.
- Eddie, I invited him.

26:21.067 --> 26:22.464
I told him he could come.

26:22.569 --> 26:26.218
He says that nobody has anything nice
to say about Joe, and I want to help.

26:26.322 --> 26:28.611
You're not saying anything to anybody.

26:29.659 --> 26:32.577
I don't want her name mentioned
in any article, understand?

26:34.831 --> 26:35.780
Now get out of here.

26:59.022 --> 26:59.887
<i>Knees up!</i>

27:10.492 --> 27:11.523
<i>Jumping jacks!</i>

28:04.337 --> 28:05.617
<i>See you next week.</i>

28:12.679 --> 28:15.619
- I'll see you guys later. I'm late.
- Great class. Thanks.

28:15.723 --> 28:16.589
'Bye.

28:17.225 --> 28:18.388
You did good.

28:19.936 --> 28:21.976
- See you later.
- Hi.

28:25.984 --> 28:28.799
- What are you doing here?
- I just thought I'd come by...

28:28.903 --> 28:31.525
and see if you needed someone
to help charge your battery.

28:35.118 --> 28:38.225
- I have a confession to make.
- A confession? Yeah?

28:38.329 --> 28:39.685
What kind of confession?

28:39.789 --> 28:43.272
On my way to work, I went to the library
and pulled some back issues...

28:43.376 --> 28:46.247
of <i>Rolling Stone</i> and read
some articles that you wrote.

28:47.964 --> 28:49.292
Really? Which ones?

28:50.425 --> 28:52.382
<i>Abscam</i> and <i>Junk Food.</i>

28:53.469 --> 28:56.174
"And?" he says, fishing for a compliment.

28:57.265 --> 28:58.973
You're pretty good.

29:00.602 --> 29:02.843
Must be fun being a reporter nowadays.

29:03.646 --> 29:06.137
"Yeah," he says suspiciously.

29:07.609 --> 29:10.100
You get to try to keep
the big boys honest.

29:10.236 --> 29:13.719
At the same time, you get to figure out
which way the culture's going.

29:13.823 --> 29:16.138
I guess that's true.
A friend of mine says...

29:16.242 --> 29:19.777
that popular culture is to society
what dreams are to an individual.

29:20.205 --> 29:24.416
If you want to find out about an individual,
you analyse their dreams.

29:25.001 --> 29:26.148
Same with society.

29:26.252 --> 29:30.416
If you want to find out about a society,
you analyse things like music and film.

29:31.216 --> 29:35.379
- Or health clubs, or junk food.
- And in doing so, you can be quite vicious.

29:38.306 --> 29:40.097
I think I try to be objective.

29:43.061 --> 29:44.888
Do you always work on a computer?

29:48.525 --> 29:50.648
Do you know anything about computers?

29:52.612 --> 29:54.301
I took a couple of courses.

29:54.405 --> 29:56.387
- You left it on.
- I always leave it on.

29:56.491 --> 30:00.358
This way, it's already warmed up
if I get an idea in the middle of the night.

30:01.746 --> 30:02.991
May I?

30:25.186 --> 30:26.709
Everybody writes that.

30:26.813 --> 30:29.545
I was hoping you'd come up
with something more original.

30:29.649 --> 30:31.108
How do you erase it?

30:49.419 --> 30:52.704
A good reporter would never get in bed
with a subject.

30:53.673 --> 30:55.333
You keep forgetting something.

30:56.551 --> 30:58.129
I'm not your subject.

31:11.774 --> 31:14.173
- You'd probably be a lousy interview.
- Probably.

31:14.277 --> 31:17.278
- No opinions, no ideas.
- None.

31:18.156 --> 31:21.722
- I think I'll take your class anyway.
- I give a very tough class.

31:21.826 --> 31:23.700
You do? Tell me about it.

31:24.537 --> 31:26.993
First, there's the warm-up.

31:28.416 --> 31:30.456
The warm-up is designed...

31:31.044 --> 31:34.994
to increase blood to the muscles,
to warm up the muscles.

31:35.632 --> 31:37.209
So as to be able...

31:37.926 --> 31:40.499
to do the more strenuous exercises.

31:41.221 --> 31:43.593
And then, there's the cardiovascular.

31:48.478 --> 31:50.138
Let me get rid of this.

31:51.940 --> 31:54.431
Hello. Yes. Who?

31:55.401 --> 31:57.026
Mr. McKenzie, yes.

31:57.946 --> 32:00.567
Well, this is he. Well, who told you?

32:01.407 --> 32:03.151
Shotsy did. Good.

32:04.452 --> 32:07.453
That's good, I think you should tell
your side of the story.

32:08.498 --> 32:11.748
Well, if I left right now,
I could probably catch the redeye.

32:12.544 --> 32:15.379
Great. Sounds good. Thank you.

32:17.340 --> 32:20.092
He'll meet with me. Maybe he'll talk.

32:21.219 --> 32:22.382
I got to go.

32:24.722 --> 32:26.098
Of course you do.

32:26.808 --> 32:28.219
Wait a minute.

32:29.185 --> 32:30.977
This is to be continued.

32:33.022 --> 32:34.398
I certainly hope so.

32:44.868 --> 32:46.598
- Hello?
- Hi, I called the office.

32:46.703 --> 32:48.350
They said you're still home.

32:48.454 --> 32:50.079
Rough night.

32:50.999 --> 32:53.689
Mikey Douglas was in town,
and I got the cocktail flu.

32:53.793 --> 32:56.118
- Where are you?
- I'm at JFK. Guess what?

32:56.337 --> 33:00.237
I got a meeting today with McKenzie.
We're to meet at 12:00 at the Atrium Club.

33:00.341 --> 33:01.697
- <i>You're shitting me.</i>
- No.

33:01.801 --> 33:04.533
- You got any space in the next issue?
- I'll make space.

33:04.637 --> 33:06.926
- <i>Has the cover closed yet?</i>
- Yeah, it's closed.

33:08.099 --> 33:09.178
Screw the cover.

33:09.517 --> 33:12.333
You're drunk, aren't you?
Must have been some turbulence.

33:12.437 --> 33:14.585
Listen, I can't talk. I got to go.

33:14.689 --> 33:18.473
I'll drop by later, how's that? 'Bye.
Wish me luck.

33:19.194 --> 33:20.688
Adam?

33:28.244 --> 33:29.620
Kent, it's Mark.

33:29.913 --> 33:33.604
Listen, I've waited all my life to say this:
Hold the presses.

33:33.708 --> 33:34.906
And get me Frankie.

33:45.595 --> 33:49.094
- What is she doing here? Frankie!
- Adam!

33:49.224 --> 33:52.206
- What are you doing?
- Mark wants me to photograph McKenzie.

33:52.310 --> 33:55.542
- No, he's nuts. I can't take you with me.
- Come on. You can try.

33:55.647 --> 33:57.770
- Forget about it.
- Adam, come on.

33:58.191 --> 33:59.838
Go, Frankie. I'm not kidding.

33:59.943 --> 34:02.466
Nobody's supposed to be here.
You'll blow it.

34:02.570 --> 34:06.679
- My photos are as important as your story.
- There'll be no story without an interview.

34:06.783 --> 34:08.443
- Don't do this to me.
- Bull!

34:09.034 --> 34:11.391
- What?
- It's Charlie, his flack.

34:11.496 --> 34:12.935
- Stay here.
- Charlie who?

34:13.039 --> 34:14.699
- Give me your camera.
- No.

34:15.083 --> 34:16.542
Charlie, hi.

34:16.835 --> 34:19.670
I'm so sorry I'm late.
The traffic was impossible.

34:24.509 --> 34:27.925
- Mind if I use my tape recorder?
- Why don't you ask him yourself?

34:33.976 --> 34:35.958
Well, you certainly come prepared.

34:36.062 --> 34:39.431
- Where to, Mr. McKenzie?
- Just drive around the park.

34:47.197 --> 34:49.523
- So, what happened?
- I got it.

34:49.659 --> 34:53.266
I never thought I'd get him to talk,
but once he started he wouldn't stop.

34:53.371 --> 34:56.145
It was amazing.
I have three solid hours all on tape.

34:56.248 --> 34:57.447
Adam!

34:58.126 --> 35:00.774
Where's my camera?
Give it to me right now.

35:00.879 --> 35:03.360
- Don't ever pull that again.
- The film's inside.

35:03.464 --> 35:05.237
- My first picture credit.
- What?

35:05.341 --> 35:08.793
- Have it developed. See you later, Frankie.
- Screw you.

35:12.182 --> 35:13.676
- So what's the story?
- Okay.

35:14.559 --> 35:18.000
McKenzie was negotiating
to sell his computers to Czechoslovakia...

35:18.104 --> 35:19.515
to save his company.

35:19.772 --> 35:22.546
He had it all worked out.
He was gonna move computers...

35:22.650 --> 35:25.299
through dummy corporations,
all over Europe...

35:25.403 --> 35:27.728
until they wound up
behind the Iron Curtain.

35:27.906 --> 35:30.721
He claims the government found out
what he was up to...

35:30.825 --> 35:33.098
and put him out of business
by busting him.

35:33.203 --> 35:35.741
- How much space do you need?
- Six pages.

35:37.248 --> 35:37.912
Four.

35:38.917 --> 35:39.782
Five.

35:40.293 --> 35:43.942
Okay, four and a half.
We'll hold the issue. When can I have it?

35:44.047 --> 35:46.289
- How soon do you need it?
- Tomorrow morning.

35:46.925 --> 35:47.873
You got it.

35:50.428 --> 35:52.618
What about this aerobics contest
coming up?

35:52.722 --> 35:54.762
They want me to make a demonstration.

35:54.891 --> 35:57.331
- Jessie, phone for you.
- Okay.

35:57.435 --> 35:59.677
- Okay, killer, I'll see you later.
- Be good.

35:59.979 --> 36:02.002
- How you doing? You through?
- Yeah.

36:02.106 --> 36:03.587
- Where were you?
- Hiding.

36:03.691 --> 36:04.854
Here you go.

36:05.902 --> 36:07.147
Hello.

36:08.613 --> 36:10.570
Adam, hi.

36:10.949 --> 36:12.775
I'm fine. How was the interview?

36:13.284 --> 36:14.932
It was real interesting.

36:15.036 --> 36:19.164
I really can't tell you the details right now.
I'm afraid this phone is being tapped.

36:19.499 --> 36:22.619
I'll be in tomorrow.
I'll call you when I know what time.

36:23.711 --> 36:24.909
I'll be there.

36:33.972 --> 36:35.964
<i>Make sure my tape recorder is on.</i>

36:37.141 --> 36:41.768
<i>I understand you suspect the government
of what lawyers politely call "misconduct."</i>

36:42.188 --> 36:43.184
<i>That's right.</i>

36:44.482 --> 36:46.771
<i>Well, could you expand on that?</i>

36:47.777 --> 36:49.633
<i>I have reason to believe...</i>

36:49.737 --> 36:53.486
<i>that they eavesdropped
on my office computers.</i>

36:53.700 --> 36:55.776
<i>You know, like hackers. But...</i>

36:55.994 --> 36:58.698
<i>these hackers weren't kids.
They were FBI hackers.</i>

37:32.405 --> 37:33.983
Yes, hello.

37:37.660 --> 37:38.858
What cuts?

37:39.871 --> 37:41.365
What trouble?

37:43.124 --> 37:44.038
Right.

37:44.626 --> 37:46.499
I'll be there. Okay.

37:57.555 --> 37:58.634
Frankie.

37:59.390 --> 38:03.851
- How did my pictures turn out?
- Bad, amateurish, snapshotty.

38:04.395 --> 38:05.510
That good?

38:07.732 --> 38:11.018
- Mark can see you. The lawyers are here.
- The lawyers?

38:16.533 --> 38:18.490
Come on in.
You know Tod Turner and Martha Young?

38:19.160 --> 38:20.489
Only on the phone.

38:21.162 --> 38:23.477
You really are expecting this
to cause trouble.

38:23.581 --> 38:25.896
- I thought you liked causing trouble.
- I do...

38:26.000 --> 38:28.456
more than anybody you know,
but up to a point.

38:28.628 --> 38:30.067
Let me guess what that is.

38:30.171 --> 38:33.028
Could that be the point
where trouble costs you money?

38:33.132 --> 38:35.531
Right. You want to split the bills
on this one?

38:35.635 --> 38:38.117
- What's the problem?
- Martha, why don't you start?

38:38.221 --> 38:40.869
Mark says that you have
the entire interview on tape.

38:40.974 --> 38:42.765
Something like three hours?

38:43.101 --> 38:45.582
- Who's to retain custody of the tapes?
- I am, why?

38:45.687 --> 38:49.387
The magazine should retain
the original tape, or a copy for its files.

38:49.816 --> 38:53.048
- That's not a problem, is it?
- That is a problem.

38:53.153 --> 38:55.801
I promised McKenzie
I wouldn't let anyone have a copy.

38:55.905 --> 38:58.762
The prosecutors will demand a copy
once this story is out.

38:58.867 --> 39:01.951
I promised him they would never get it.
I gave him my word.

39:02.412 --> 39:05.269
We'll do everything to keep the tapes
from the government.

39:05.373 --> 39:08.981
- We'll fight any subpoena in court.
- That's not good enough.

39:09.085 --> 39:13.165
I will make sure the tapes don't get out.
The only way to do that is to keep them.

39:14.507 --> 39:18.505
What happens if the magazine were fined
$1,000 a day until you turned them over?

39:19.679 --> 39:22.369
I won't test the magazine's guts
or its bank account.

39:22.473 --> 39:25.391
The government could pressure you, too,
send you to jail.

39:25.602 --> 39:29.053
That's a risk I have to take.
Where are the cuts? I want to see them.

39:29.981 --> 39:31.211
Adam, be reasonable.

39:31.316 --> 39:34.381
You could have libelled McKenzie.
He could have libelled others.

39:34.486 --> 39:37.819
Let's not kid around.
Mark could be facing millions in lawsuits.

39:38.907 --> 39:41.943
Without your tapes we have no evidence
to go into court with.

39:43.077 --> 39:46.696
I can't recommend that Mark publish
the article unless you turn them over.

39:46.998 --> 39:50.314
I can't recommend these cuts.
Someone's editing with their elbows.

39:50.418 --> 39:52.024
- Where are the tapes?
- In my bag.

39:52.128 --> 39:55.235
Look, you wanted me to do the story,
I did the story. Okay?

39:55.340 --> 39:58.091
Take it or leave it.
Print it, don't print it.

39:58.426 --> 40:01.297
I got a plane to catch.
Another story to write.

40:06.434 --> 40:08.178
You have a big decision to make.

40:23.076 --> 40:24.903
Now, where were we?

40:34.838 --> 40:36.960
What comes after the warm-up?

40:37.340 --> 40:38.715
After the warm-up...

40:39.467 --> 40:41.958
is the cardiovascular section.

40:42.512 --> 40:44.801
It should last for 15 to 20 minutes.

40:45.265 --> 40:48.384
It should be un-interrupted and steady.

40:49.477 --> 40:54.169
This aerobic phase exercises
the most important muscle in the body.

40:54.274 --> 40:56.017
- Which is?
- The heart.

45:25.461 --> 45:27.234
- How do you feel?
- I feel great.

45:27.338 --> 45:29.960
- You're gonna be sore tomorrow.
- I don't think so.

45:30.466 --> 45:33.467
- Still want to interview me?
- I don't know.

45:33.761 --> 45:36.452
- I broke the cardinal rule of journalism.
- What's that?

45:36.556 --> 45:39.830
After what we did last night,
I don't think I can be objective.

45:39.934 --> 45:42.666
- I need to take a shower.
- I need to make a phone call.

45:42.770 --> 45:45.096
- You want to come out to my house later?
- Yeah.

45:45.648 --> 45:47.308
- You did good today.
- Thanks.

45:47.609 --> 45:48.937
For a New Yorker.

45:49.861 --> 45:52.269
- For a New Yorker, too.
- Nice legs.

45:55.116 --> 45:57.738
- Mark, it's Adam!
- I'll take it up here.

46:01.706 --> 46:04.279
- Tell him I have to talk to him.
- Hello.

46:04.584 --> 46:08.451
